Package org.jtuples

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Tuple
    Represents a mathematical tuple.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractTuple
    This class provides skeletal implementations of common methods for tuples.
    Decuple<A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,I,J>
    Represents a mathematical ordered decuple of objects.
    Functions
    This class provides static methods to support a functional programming style.
    Nonuple<A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,I>
    Represents a mathematical ordered nonuple of objects.
    Octuple<A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H>
    Represents a mathematical ordered octuple of objects.
    Pair<A,B>
    Represents a mathematical ordered pair of objects.
    Quadruple<A,B,C,D>
    Represents a mathematical ordered quadruple of objects.
    Quintuple<A,B,C,D,E>
    Represents a mathematical ordered quintuple of objects.
    Septuple<A,B,C,D,E,F,G>
    Represents a mathematical ordered septuple of objects.
    Sextuple<A,B,C,D,E,F>
    Represents a mathematical ordered sextuple of objects.
    Triple<A,B,C>
    Represents a mathematical ordered triple of objects.
    Tuples
    This class consists exclusively of static methods that return or operate on tuples.
